    <section name="Welcome to Terradue's OpenSource Software repository!">
      <p>Terradue is the company with a new vision to the production, management and distribution of spatial data where
      cloud technology joins geographical data inventory and query systems, carried out collaboratively with best-known
      open source projects.</p>

      <subsection name="Open Source projects">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Component</th><th></th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="http://terradue.github.com/dsione-tools/">dsione-tools</a></td>
              <td>CLI tools for OpenNebula to interact with DSI</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="http://terradue.github.com/FindThenFetch/">FindThenFetch</a></td>
              <td>OpenSearch client written in Perl</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="http://terradue.github.com/jcatalogue-client/">jcatalogue-client</a></td>
              <td>a REST client APIs set for OpenSearch Geo and Temporal protocol servers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="http://terradue.github.com/xiongnu/">xiongnu</a></td>
              <td>Couchbase prototype catalogue</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="http://terradue.github.com/opennebula-occi-tsystems/">opennebula-occi-tsystems</a></td>
              <td>An OpenNebula extension to bridge OpenNebula to t-systems Dynamic Service for Infrastructure (DSI)
              via OCCI API</td>
